Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.72,0:32:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,people just for the glee of killing.\NJust for the glee of killing.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.88,0:32:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,H\Nso
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.88,0:32:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,man ow owns owes his survival to\Ntestosterone
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.88,0:32:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and he owes\Now owes about 90% of his pain to the
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.48,0:32:30.79,Default,,0,0,0,,same testosterone\Nand learning how to handle one's
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.79,0:32:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,testosterone is the most difficult part\Nof being a male.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.96,0:32:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It's also a very difficult part of being\Na female
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.32,0:32:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,handling his testosterone and\Nnow they find that women need some
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.20,0:32:48.55,Default,,0,0,0,,testosterone of their own and or else\Nthey got complaints to the doctor you
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.55,0:32:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,know.\NSo how to balance that? How to envision
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.03,0:33:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that? How to keep it in balance?\NTherefore, love leads to
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.72,0:33:10.08,Default,,0,0,0,,uh the capacity for\Nreverence
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.08,0:33:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,for that which is intrinsic and innate\Nwithin the spirit of one's
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.44,0:33:19.60,Default,,0,0,0,,partner.\NCan be more than one partner. You can
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.60,0:33:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,certainly love many in a lifetime.\NSo that's part of the evolution of human
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.84,0:33:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness to come out of matingness\Ninto maternal survival
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.36,0:33:41.51,Default,,0,0,0,,into servitude to the male then\Nembargoning that servitude for
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.51,0:33:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,commitment\Nthen transcending that to
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.08,0:33:53.84,Default,,0,0,0,,romance. Huh?\NIs romance based on first an illusion
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.84,0:33:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and then the illusion wears off and now\Nyou both look raggedy because you see
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.84,0:34:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,how it is?\NOr was the love reality? Which is which?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.44,0:34:12.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?\NI always think it's the opposite the way
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.39,0:34:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,the world sees it. I think when you\Nfirst see that person and flash on them,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.63,0:34:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,that's reality.\NThat's not illusion. The world says,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.56,0:34:25.83,Default,,0,0,0,,"Well, that's illusion." No, that's\Nreality. You get who they really are
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.83,0:34:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,because the naked self is\Nlove itself. You see what they are
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.76,0:34:38.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and you fall instantly in love with that\Nenergy within them. Then as time goes
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.63,0:34:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,on, the ego raises its ugly head and\Nbegins to demean it.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.15,0:34:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,But in the beginning, you really saw\Nthem as they were. You saw their
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.28,0:34:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,incredible perfection and beauty.\Nand stunning handsomeness or whatever it
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.80,0:34:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,is that attracted you to that person.\NThen the ego comes up with its
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.04,0:35:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,self-interest and selfishness and it's\Nyour fault and blame and you forgot the
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.96,0:35:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,forks. You ruined the picnic. You forgot\Nthe forks.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.64,0:35:11.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You always blame me for everything.\NWell, why shouldn't I? You aren't to the
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.35,0:35:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,blame for everything all the time.\NYeah, but you're to blame for blaming
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.24,0:35:19.59,Default,,0,0,0,,me.\NYou're to blame for blaming me for
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.59,0:35:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,blaming you. And there it goes downhill.\NSo you have to draw back once in a while
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.80,0:35:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and see what was the reality I saw.\NIt is still there. Of course it's still
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.35,0:35:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,there. Of course it's still there.\Nrecapture the love and reverence which
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.44,0:35:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,you have for each other's existence.\NOn the log of calibrated level of
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.35,0:35:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness, we list emotions. Some\Nare very high and yet and some are
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.35,0:36:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,lesser. We got the wrong one on again.\NAnyway, how can that be? So, it's become
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.64,0:36:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,diff different aspects of our\Npersonality are at different levels. Our
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.04,0:36:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,personalities are complex. It's not just\None uni un unitized
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.80,0:36:17.83,Default,,0,0,0,,uh singularity. It's a complexity. We're\Nthe composite of all our identifications
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.83,0:36:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,as we grew up. All the people that\Nimpress us that we wanted to be like the
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.76,0:36:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,ego ideal\Nuh various influences, teachers, people
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.64,0:36:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,of inspiration in our life. Uh so we\Nhave different aspects of our
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.35,0:36:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,personality at different levels of\Nemotional development. One aspect of us
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.64,0:36:40.56,Default,,0,0,0,,can be quite evolved and another quite\Nchildish.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.56,0:36:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You know the healer in us could be quite\Nevolved.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.16,0:36:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The teacher in us, the musician,\Nthe stalwart,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.16,0:36:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,the hero.\NMost of us go through lifetimes where we
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.07,0:37:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,perfect different aspects.\NThe warrior
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.52,0:37:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,uh and some we recall as you go ahead in\Nconsciousness you begin to intuit it
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.72,0:37:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,you know how you got to be that way and\Nyou begin to even start to remember it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.07,0:37:19.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean you know very well you did such\Nand such or you wouldn't be the way you
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.83,0:37:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,are about that particular thing. is like\Na knowingness begins to take over and
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.56,0:37:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,you begin to remember.\NSo one's overall level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.11,0:37:36.24,Default,,0,0,0,,could be quite high and still an\Nemotionality could come up. Well, where
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.24,0:37:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,does that emotionality coming out of?\NIt's probably coming out of the persona.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.80,0:37:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, the persona is that\Nsuperficial level of your personality
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.24,0:37:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,which is not really what you are. You\Nknow, somebody cuts in you in traffic
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.44,0:37:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and you say, "I got to kill that guy."\NWell, you don't really mean that. If I
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.07,0:37:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,give you a gun now, say you're going to\Nkill him and I'm just talking. So,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.16,0:38:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,there's those superficial emotional\Nreactions, but that isn't who you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.32,0:38:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Who you are is based on your spiritual\Ndecisions.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.32,0:38:12.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It's your spiritual the spiritual will.\NSo, level of consciousness denotes
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.16,0:38:17.83,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual decision and will and\Nalignment. If you are aligned with that
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.83,0:38:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,which supports life and supports\Nintegrity and supports that which
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.00,0:38:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,respects the sacred and reverences life,\Nyou are in a very high place. Annoyances
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.44,0:38:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,will come up, but they don't mean\Nanything. And don't forget, we're a
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.20,0:38:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,karmic inheritance of all the\Nweirdos that live before this lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.76,0:38:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So those little memories come up. I\Nthink sometimes they come up to be
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.52,0:38:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,healed, to be recognized, to be\Nacknowledged
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.80,0:39:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and become they keep us from becoming\Negotistical that we're still capable of
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.11,0:39:05.83,Default,,0,0,0,,making mistakes. Keeps us from being\Nholier than now. It keeps us from being
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.83,0:39:09.83,Default,,0,0,0,,judgmental about the sheer humanness of\Nother people.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.83,0:39:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and uh compassionate.\NUm,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.88,0:39:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,do we have to suffer for what the\Ndinosaurs did? Well,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.07,0:39:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,some of these reverse cause and effect.\NYou see, events in the world are the
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.96,0:39:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,consequence of what happens in\Nconsciousness. Somebody says, "Well,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.32,0:39:42.16,Default,,0,0,0,,what would happen to the consciousness\Nof mankind if we had a war now?"
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.16,0:39:45.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing.\NBecause there's consciousness of mankind
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.35,0:39:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,where it is now that would manifest as\Nwar.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.96,0:39:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn't the other way around. So, World\NWar II did not alter the level of
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.80,0:39:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness of mankind at all. It was\Nexpressing where it was at at the time
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.56,0:40:04.56,Default,,0,0,0,,that the great majority of the people\Nwould go for what was sold to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.56,0:40:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if consciousness is below 200,\Nit's pretty easy to sell it that which
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.40,0:40:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,is non- integrous.\NDon't forget the great avatar said,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.40,0:40:19.59,Default,,0,0,0,,"Your third eye is not open yet. You for\Nyour own sake do not know the thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.59,0:40:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is good and that which is\Nwicked between truth and falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.28,0:40:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, you need the guru. You need\Nthe teacher. You need the great avatar.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.11,0:40:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You need the savior.\Nuntil consciousness reaches the third
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.20,0:40:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,eye and the Buddha body opens up and\Nit's clear that which is wicked and that
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.52,0:40:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,which is not wicked.\NI think we should take a break because
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.83,0:40:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm getting uh work out here folks.\NYou know, this is a great spiritual
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.72,0:40:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,group and I love being here and they\Ncome up with all these wonderful
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.68,0:41:03.83,Default,,0,0,0,,thoughts and uh\NI thank you for all the questions. We'll
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.83,0:41:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,take a break and then\Nwe'll answer some more some more
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.24,0:41:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,questions and then we'll greet people\Nand sign books and all.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.72,0:41:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I wasn't done with sexuality.\NOh yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.04,0:41:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Sexuality like money are things that\Nevery and eating meat are are the three
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.59,0:41:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,traditional things that everybody has to\Ngo through when you become a spiritual
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.68,0:41:40.56,Default,,0,0,0,,aspirin. What about eating meat? What\Nabout sex? What about money? You know,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.56,0:41:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Ramach Krishna handle it easily. He said\Nthey're all forbidden.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.88,0:41:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So I decided not to become a Rama\NKrishna devote at an early age.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.04,0:41:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,He only took young men. You weren't\Nallowed to touch money and have sex.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.28,0:42:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Right? Okay.\NSex like money mean we're talking about
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.92,0:42:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,attachments to be run by something to be\Nrun by desires. So sex and money are no
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.56,0:42:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,different than any other thing. Um,\Ndesiring this attachment is the same to
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.28,0:42:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,what you're attached is really\Nirrelevant. Whether it's sex or money
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.48,0:42:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't really make any difference.\NThere is a point in spiritual
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.00,0:42:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,development where the the energy begin\Nthe energy of life begins to rise
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.20,0:42:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,through the chakras and there may be a\Nsurprising period of life when sex just
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.56,0:42:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,sort of drives you crazy. You feel like\Nhypersexual.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.24,0:42:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because the energy of life which is\Nrising as it rises energizes each chakra
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.76,0:42:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,including the base chakra and of course\Nthen it gets to the heart and love
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.16,0:42:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,becomes more predominant. It then it\Ngets to the third eye and then you're
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.96,0:43:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,done with all that but\Nit's that you're not run by it.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.96,0:43:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,We see you sneaking in late.\NIt's not being run by it. So the freedom
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.16,0:43:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,to enjoy one's biologic heritage of\Ncourse is part of the joy of being a
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.92,0:43:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,human being. Part of the expression of\Nthe joy of life, the exuberance of life
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.07,0:43:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and um to not be entrapped by it. That's\Nall. The same with money. We can have
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.35,0:43:35.11,Default,,0,0,0,,money or not have money. It's all the\Nsame. It's really all the same. Whether
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.11,0:43:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,you have lots of it or you don't have\Nany of it, it's all the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.76,0:43:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You can be very, very rich on Monday,\Nleave it all on Tuesday, and life is
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.52,0:43:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,really not different at all. You're\Ndriving down the highway enjoying life,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.20,0:43:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and there's the birds and the bees, and\Nnothing's changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.64,0:43:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Not a thing has changed.\NSo, it's the attachment to it, the being
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.56,0:44:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,run by it. It's okay to have it. It's\Nokay to not have it.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.52,0:44:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody asked about sexuality. The sage\Nat that point, one has just transcended
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.16,0:44:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,it. You can either have it or not have\Nit. That's like money or sex is is it's
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.96,0:44:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,great when you have it and it's great\Nwhen you don't have it. If you've got a
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.68,0:44:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,wonderful dinner cooked for for for\Ndinner tonight, it's fantastic. And if
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.72,0:44:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,you have peanut butter sandwiches, it's\Nall the same. You know what I mean? So,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.48,0:44:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the enjoyment of life comes out of the\Njoy of one's existence from every
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.56,0:44:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,moment, not from anything that's out\Nthere. There's nothing out there that
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.96,0:44:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,can give you joy. The only thing\Nsomething out there can do is satisfy
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.68,0:44:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the desiringness is blocking the\Nexperience of joy. So when you satisfy
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.72,0:44:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,that, what happens is that which is\Nblocking the experience of your own
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.16,0:44:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,inner self is removed. Now you feel the\Nradiance of your own inner self coming
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.31,0:44:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,forth as joy and happiness.\NYou think that the happiness is coming
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.56,0:44:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,from the thing you just got. No, the\Nthing that you just got. shut up that
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.68,0:45:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,which was interfering with the\Nexperience of the joy of the presence of
Dialogue: 0,0:45:03.76,0:45:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the self within. There's only one source\Nof joy and that's the presence of God
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.88,0:45:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,within.\NIt's periodically experienced. If you
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.16,0:45:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,ascribe\Ncausation to out thereess, then you get
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.80,0:45:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,attached to out there.\NIf the only time you feel joyful is a
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.59,0:45:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,sexual conquest, then you get attached\Nto the out there of it all, the same as
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.76,0:45:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,with drugs or any other addiction or\Nattachment. To be free of it means it's
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.76,0:45:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,okay if you have it and it's okay if you\Ndon't. If you have hamburgers, hot dogs,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.24,0:45:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,or peanut butter sandwiches,\Nit doesn't make any difference because
Dialogue: 0,0:45:46.48,0:45:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,it's all\Nthe source of joy is eventually
Dialogue: 0,0:45:51.68,0:45:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,continuous. The sure of joy comes from\Nthe awareness of the source of your own
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.56,0:46:01.59,Default,,0,0,0,,existence. The presence of God within\Nyou gives you a certain radiance to
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.59,0:46:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,one's inner experience.\NThe inner experience of one's own
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.44,0:46:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,existence itself becomes continuously\Njoyful.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.04,0:46:17.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So it doesn't matter what you do out\Nthere. If they say today you die, you
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.83,0:46:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,say, "Man, fantastic.\NBeen looking forward to this for a
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.64,0:46:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,lifetime." You know what I'm saying?\NYou remember going out of body, man? It
Dialogue: 0,0:46:29.92,0:46:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,was cool. So in other words, everything,\Nno matter what happens, is fine. They
Dialogue: 0,0:46:33.76,0:46:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,say you're not dying today. You say,\N"Oh, fantastic. I can enjoy another day
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.92,0:46:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,of staying alive." Either way, it's all\Nthe same.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.80,0:46:50.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh,\None surreners the source of joy
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.31,0:46:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,from out there to the awareness that its\Nsource is only from within. That comes
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.11,0:47:01.59,Default,,0,0,0,,about through spiritual evolution.\NThat makes you independent of such
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.59,0:47:07.68,Default,,0,0,0,,experiences. If they happen, it's great.\NAnd if they don't happen, it's great.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.68,0:47:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a lot of why questions.\NNever ask why.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.88,0:47:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Why? Because\Nyou understand why is the hypothetical.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.16,0:47:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The why of anything is the hypothetical.\NWhy is man what he is? Why is God what
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.59,0:47:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,he is? Why does the spirit only come in\Nthe embryo in the third month? Why do a
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.28,0:47:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,whole lot of people die in one big\Ndisaster?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.11,0:47:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You see it's a mind game. Why is a mind\Ngame?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.92,0:47:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You cannot understand the nonlinear\Nspiritual reality
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.88,0:48:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,from the limitation of Newtonian\Nparadigm and logic.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.00,0:48:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The linear cannot explain the nonlinear.\NThe stretching of it to try to make it
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.96,0:48:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,do so ends up with a serious\Ndistortion of spiritual vision.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:19.11,0:48:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a pseudo explanation\Nand it's not a reality. It does not ring
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.00,0:48:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,true. As plausible as it may sound, it\Nis not the whess of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.83,0:48:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,There are no wise in spiritual reality.\NYou see the endlessness of why.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:41.28,0:48:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I can add any thought, any observation\Nthroughout all of human history and
Dialogue: 0,0:48:46.72,0:48:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,prefix it with why.\NWhy the revolution? Why World War II?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:51.92,0:48:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Why human beings? Why whites, blacks,\Nand colors and various hues that we come
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.31,0:49:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,in? Why blondes and brunettes? Why blue\Neyes and brown eyes? Why two feet? Why
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.64,0:49:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,not four feet? You know, why anything?\NWhy is a question for idiots?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:08.96,0:49:14.07,Default,,0,0,0,,comes from a total insanity.\NThere is no why to anything, folks.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.07,0:49:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,There's only what is. It is that way.\NGod doesn't know why either.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:25.76,0:49:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,God is a giant electromagnetic field\Nabout all this and all this is twizzing
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.44,0:49:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,around in there. And you ask him why.\NHow the heck did I know? It's just the
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.44,0:49:38.16,Default,,0,0,0,,way it is.\NI am what I am and therefore everything
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.16,0:49:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,is the way it is and that's sufficient\Nright
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.24,0:49:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,you surrender your will to God you don't\Nneed a why you just accept the isness of
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.48,0:49:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,what appears to be and then later on you\Nfind out what appears to be isn't that
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.31,0:49:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,way anyway so\Nfor instance why do these various things
Dialogue: 0,0:49:56.80,0:50:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,in the Bible calibrated this and this I\Ndon't know why
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.72,0:50:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the Old Testament there's three books\Nthat calibrate over 200
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.96,0:50:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't the others? How the hell did I\Nknow? I didn't write the I didn't write
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.96,0:50:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,the Old Testament. You know what I mean?\NI don't know what this says. Something
Dialogue: 0,0:50:30.16,0:50:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,about still small voices. I don't know.\NAnd are they speaking about children?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.11,0:50:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what it means. Well, the\Nknowingness of spiritual awareness, I
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.83,0:50:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,think, is what they're referring to.\NYes. Yes. Because the knowingness of
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.40,0:50:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual awareness comes about as a\Nknowingness, a different style of
Dialogue: 0,0:50:54.55,0:50:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,learning. You see, because of schooling,\Nwe think of linear progressive
Dialogue: 0,0:50:59.83,0:51:08.07,Default,,0,0,0,,schooling. third grade, fourth grade, we\Nthink of of it as a linear progression.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.07,0:51:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritual knowingness, learningness is\Ntotally different. It comes out of
Dialogue: 0,0:51:13.20,0:51:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,nothing at all and\Nand becomes obvious
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.88,0:51:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,with no intercert stages. It isn't like\Nyou see a little bit here on Monday.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:23.59,0:51:27.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Wednesday it gets a little clearer.\NFriday, ah, now I see it. It's you work
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.35,0:51:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,on it over the weekend and Monday you\Ngot it down pat.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.96,0:51:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,No, you're riding a horse and you're\Nworried about your rump
Dialogue: 0,0:51:34.64,0:51:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and all of a sudden it's clear to you\Nwhy something is why it is. It's an
Dialogue: 0,0:51:42.40,0:51:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,idiotic question. So\Nthe still small voice is sort of a
Dialogue: 0,0:51:50.72,0:51:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,knowingness.\NWhen we were talking about karma, we
Dialogue: 0,0:51:54.16,0:51:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,said, you know, it's a belief system to\Nsome people. It's not a belief system.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.88,0:52:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Forget about it.\NForget about karma. Just forget about
Dialogue: 0,0:52:02.55,0:52:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,it.\NIt's easier if you know something about
Dialogue: 0,0:52:05.92,0:52:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,it. But if you know anything about it,\Nit'll still work out.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:10.88,0:52:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,May take you a couple hundred thousand\Nlifetimes more, but it'll work out.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:19.44,0:52:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,See, because the western world without\Nthe awareness of karma doesn't
Dialogue: 0,0:52:22.40,0:52:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,understand that every single thought,\Nmove, decision has a consequence.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:28.96,0:52:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Has a consequence.\NNot a punishment, not not something
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.00,0:52:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,negative and horrible, but everything\Nyou do has a consequence whether you
Dialogue: 0,0:52:38.24,0:52:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,like it or not.\NNow the idiot says why?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:43.83,0:52:48.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Because that's the nature of the\Nuniverse that everything that happens
Dialogue: 0,0:52:48.55,0:52:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,has a consequence to the totality of the\Nwhole. See, as we've explained it before
Dialogue: 0,0:52:54.88,0:53:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and the whole universe, this this\Nplanet's here and this planet's here.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:00.07,0:53:04.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, this planet's being here does not\Ncause this planet to be here. But if
Dialogue: 0,0:53:04.31,0:53:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,this planet wasn't here, this planet\Nwouldn't be where it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.48,0:53:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Each one of us affects the totality of\Nyou might say the density of the whole
Dialogue: 0,0:53:14.48,0:53:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,as a consequence of which the buoyancy\Nof all of us is affected.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:19.44,0:53:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So each spirit each soul is like a cork\Nin the sea and as it makes these choices
Dialogue: 0,0:53:24.72,0:53:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,it rises and falls depending on\Nits choices the size of the cork and the
Dialogue: 0,0:53:32.24,0:53:39.04,Default,,0,0,0,,density of the sea.\NMhm. Here's
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.04,0:53:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,some things I didn't ask about. I'll do\Nthat sometime when I'm home privately.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:46.64,0:53:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh there's questions about channeling.\NYou know, some people think that when I
Dialogue: 0,0:53:52.00,0:53:57.59,Default,,0,0,0,,talk I'm channeling. Somebody will say,\N"Where do you channel it from?"
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.59,0:54:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,In channeling there's a this and a that.\NThere's a me and a you or this and an
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.92,0:54:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,it.\NThere's two different entities.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:05.92,0:54:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Um\Nchanneling to me is risky because you
Dialogue: 0,0:54:09.52,0:54:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,don't know what's on the other side and\Nwhat level of other another dimension
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.24,0:54:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,it's coming from. Lower astral, middle,\Nhigher or celestial. You have no idea
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.48,0:54:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,unless you're pretty good at\Nkinesiologic calibration and you can
Dialogue: 0,0:54:22.16,0:54:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrate the energy of that entity on\Nthe other side. If it was a really high
Dialogue: 0,0:54:26.00,0:54:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,entity, it wouldn't be doing any\Nchanneling in the first place
Dialogue: 0,0:54:30.16,0:54:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,cuz no need to control. I'll tell you\Nsomething about this world. All the
Dialogue: 0,0:54:34.07,0:54:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual information you'll ever need\Nhas already been spoken.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:39.20,0:54:43.11,Default,,0,0,0,,There is nothing more needed than what\Nhas been said. Even what has been said
Dialogue: 0,0:54:43.11,0:54:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,this day, there's nothing more needed.\NConsequently, to search elsewhere is a
Dialogue: 0,0:54:50.48,0:54:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,way of evading spiritual reality,\Nspiritual truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:55.20,0:55:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't need a strange name on the\Nother side telling you weird things.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:00.00,0:55:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. And a lot of it is weird. I'll\Ntell you, you don't need strange beings
Dialogue: 0,0:55:04.80,0:55:08.07,Default,,0,0,0,,elsewhere.\NDon't trust anything unless it's in a
Dialogue: 0,0:55:08.07,0:55:14.31,Default,,0,0,0,,body. Unless you can see it or unless\Nit's been in the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:14.31,0:55:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The spiritual real the spiritual truth\Nthat need that the that the human being
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.96,0:55:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,needs has already been spoken. Nothing\Nmore is needed. It was spoken thousands
Dialogue: 0,0:55:24.88,0:55:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,of years ago.\NNothing more is needed.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:29.68,0:55:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The course of miracles came about in a\Nrather unique way. I I knew uh Bill and
Dialogue: 0,0:55:35.44,0:55:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew uh Helen.\NHelen herself, you know, didn't really
Dialogue: 0,0:55:40.40,0:55:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,believe in the course of miracles. It\Nwas strange. You know, Helen was the
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.59,0:55:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,secretary.\NShe said she got it through inner
Dialogue: 0,0:55:48.96,0:55:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,dictation. It was not some other entity\Nelsewhere. She didn't hear it from
Dialogue: 0,0:55:54.72,0:55:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,elsewhere. It came about as an inner\Nknowingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:59.11,0:56:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,which came about due to a prior\Nagreement before she came in this
Dialogue: 0,0:56:03.20,0:56:06.31,Default,,0,0,0,,lifetime. She agreed to take the\Ninterdictation. She called it
Dialogue: 0,0:56:06.31,0:56:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,interdictation. It came as a progressive\Nunfolding of a knowingness in a lady who
Dialogue: 0,0:56:11.44,0:56:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I will tell you and she would not be\Ninsulted if she were in the audience
Dialogue: 0,0:56:14.72,0:56:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,right now had about this much spiritual\Nawareness.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:20.48,0:56:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,How of that dimension could get such an\Nincredible uh language of truth is is
Dialogue: 0,0:56:26.96,0:56:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,mindboggling. But that was her\Nagreement. She said, "I agreed to be the
Dialogue: 0,0:56:32.31,0:56:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,um it was innerdictation\Ncame about as a strange form of an inner
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.76,0:56:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,knowingness apparently by contract I\Nwould suppose by somebody in some
Dialogue: 0,0:56:43.92,0:56:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,celestial realm. That would be my\Npresumption.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:47.76,0:56:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,sure she herself didn't live by it and\Nwas uh
Dialogue: 0,0:56:54.07,0:57:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,a different kind of person.\NBill on the other hand, Bill Feford who
Dialogue: 0,0:57:01.04,0:57:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,worked with her on getting it into\Nwritten form was pretty heart kind of a
Dialogue: 0,0:57:06.55,0:57:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,person, you know.\NSo it was just she her commitment was to
Dialogue: 0,0:57:12.24,0:57:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,be the secretary and it just came to her\Nlike an inner dictation and that she
Dialogue: 0,0:57:17.04,0:57:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,just typed it out as it came into her\Nhead. A rather incredible piece of work
Dialogue: 0,0:57:21.20,0:57:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,to get in that mode of of uh\Ntransmission. I don't know if anything
Dialogue: 0,0:57:26.24,0:57:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,else has really been transmitted that\Nway. But of course I don't read a lot of
Dialogue: 0,0:57:29.68,0:57:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,things. In fact I don't read anything to\Nbe truthful with you. So I can't be an
Dialogue: 0,0:57:34.24,0:57:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,expert on that. But uh I did know Helen\Nand um I knew her quite well. So anyway,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:41.04,0:57:46.16,Default,,0,0,0,,that's how it came about and all we know\Nis that it calibrates at 600 and that
Dialogue: 0,0:57:46.16,0:57:50.79,Default,,0,0,0,,those who have followed it have\Nexperienced the experiential truth that
Dialogue: 0,0:57:50.79,0:57:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,lies behind it.\NUm
Dialogue: 0,0:57:56.00,0:57:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,this is another u these are all why\Nquestions. They're coming from some kind
Dialogue: 0,0:57:59.92,0:58:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,of a why person.\NAnd the person who's addicted to
Dialogue: 0,0:58:05.04,0:58:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,whininess\Nwho may remain anonymous.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:12.31,0:58:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Quiness will lead you downward rather\Nthan upward. It will lead you to greater
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.44,0:58:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and greater illusion.\NBecause if there is no legitimate answer
Dialogue: 0,0:58:22.55,0:58:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,to why, the mind will create a facious\None and your mind will be filled with
Dialogue: 0,0:58:27.28,0:58:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,facious answers to wise. A why is\Nhypothetical. That which is hypothetical
Dialogue: 0,0:58:32.79,0:58:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,has no existence in reality.\N>> Would you like to answer this?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:47.83,0:58:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Okay.\N>> That which is the hypothetical does not
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.20,0:58:56.96,Default,,0,0,0,,exist in the real existence. All right.\NOkay. You got it. The hypothetical does
Dialogue: 0,0:58:56.96,0:59:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,not exist in the real. Therefore, you\Ncannot make spiritual progress by asking
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.72,0:59:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,the question why. You can only go\Ndownward into further and further
Dialogue: 0,0:59:05.44,0:59:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,illusion\Nbecause the ego will manufacture an
Dialogue: 0,0:59:09.44,0:59:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,answer to the why in order to maintain\Nits hold of your mind. You have to let
Dialogue: 0,0:59:14.72,0:59:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,go of being addicted to the whess.\NThe way to get rid of whessiness is to
Dialogue: 0,0:59:19.92,0:59:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,surrender not knowingness to God.\NTo become enlightened, you don't have to
Dialogue: 0,0:59:26.40,0:59:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,know anything.\Nthe willingness to surrender oneself to
Dialogue: 0,0:59:31.92,0:59:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,God from moment to moment. You don't\Nhave to know anything. There's not a
Dialogue: 0,0:59:37.04,0:59:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,single why you need to know. Not a one.\NCan na karma be nullified?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:51.52,1:00:02.79,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yeah. 50 bucks.\NWrite
Dialogue: 0,1:00:02.79,1:00:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,a check. It's my favorite charity.\NThat's the way it's done in some places
Dialogue: 0,1:00:08.96,1:00:14.31,Default,,0,0,0,,in this world. Has been traditionally.\NWrite a check.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:14.31,1:00:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we make fun of it, but the writing\Nof a check is one way that one can and
Dialogue: 0,1:00:20.24,1:00:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,it's traditionally done to people who've\Nmade great sums of money and become
Dialogue: 0,1:00:24.00,1:00:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,philanthropic as they got older.\NSome people think they're buying trying
Dialogue: 0,1:00:28.24,1:00:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,to buy their way in heaven. No, it can.\NI think it can be legitimate. You begin
Dialogue: 0,1:00:32.07,1:00:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,to realize that you do owe the world\Nsomething back for what it has given
Dialogue: 0,1:00:36.31,1:00:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,you.\NSo, it can be more than just gift. It
Dialogue: 0,1:00:40.64,1:00:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,can also be the real dawning of a\Nspiritual awareness
Dialogue: 0,1:00:44.88,1:00:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,because as you get into your 80s, you\Nbegin to realize you really ought to get
Dialogue: 0,1:00:49.28,1:00:57.83,Default,,0,0,0,,serious about this spiritual business.\NWhen they start trying to sell you
Dialogue: 0,1:00:57.83,1:01:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,burial insurance you get every day in\Nthe mail.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:02.16,1:01:08.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, maybe I'll go back to church after\Nall. I mean, what's to lose? You know
Dialogue: 0,1:01:08.07,1:01:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,why? Oh, here's another why question.\NWhy do cathedrals calibrate highly?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:14.24,1:01:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we can't answer that.\NNo, this is really asking, do inanimate
Dialogue: 0,1:01:23.20,1:01:28.07,Default,,0,0,0,,objects, are they calibratable? Yes,\Nthey are. You can calibrate the energy
Dialogue: 0,1:01:28.07,1:01:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,of locations, people, inventions,\Nthoughts, feelings. this um structure
Dialogue: 0,1:01:33.35,1:01:38.79,Default,,0,0,0,,here.\NDon't forget the intention, spiritual
Dialogue: 0,1:01:38.79,1:01:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,intention is what sets the level of\Nconsciousness. So the spiritual
Dialogue: 0,1:01:43.04,1:01:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,intention to glorify God and reflect God\Nand worship God and to provide a place
Dialogue: 0,1:01:47.59,1:01:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,for others to worship and acknowledge\Nthe sovereignty of God.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:53.59,1:01:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,uh the great cathedral then it\Nrepresents the collective inspiration of
Dialogue: 0,1:01:59.20,1:02:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,a whole society, a whole civilization.\NSome of those cathedrals are so costly
Dialogue: 0,1:02:04.72,1:02:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,it really took the earnings of the\Nentire population for generations to
Dialogue: 0,1:02:09.92,1:02:14.07,Default,,0,0,0,,create it.\NGreat sacrifice,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:14.07,1:02:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,whole lifetime spent in worshiping God\Nby devotion in the form of service. You
Dialogue: 0,1:02:19.68,1:02:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,might say karma yoga to haul all those\Nblocks of marble
Dialogue: 0,1:02:24.79,1:02:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,in the hot sun\Nfor the sake of the glorification of God
Dialogue: 0,1:02:29.76,1:02:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,in itself is quite a spiritual\Nact is it not?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:37.83,1:02:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So the cathedrals are\Nthe coalition of the concordance of
Dialogue: 0,1:02:44.00,1:02:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,multiple art forms\Nuh painting, sculpture, architecture,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:51.04,1:02:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,music, incense, stained glass windows,\Nthe design of the floors, as you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:56.72,1:03:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the design of the floors, the way the\Nsquares are set, etc. The mosaic etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:02.00,1:03:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The Alhhamra which is uh not Christian\Nthe Mhamra calibrates very high anything
Dialogue: 0,1:03:07.83,1:03:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,that's that represents the collective\Ndevotion of mankind
Dialogue: 0,1:03:13.04,1:03:19.20,Default,,0,0,0,,to reflect the reality of divinity as\Nbest can it can be reflected within our
Dialogue: 0,1:03:19.20,1:03:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,human domain is respectful worshipful\Nand sacred.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:24.72,1:03:28.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Then it becomes sanctified by the\Nprayers of those who have worshiped
Dialogue: 0,1:03:28.79,1:03:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,there over the\Nmany years. And some of the cathedral, I
Dialogue: 0,1:03:34.00,1:03:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,mean, I've been in cathedrals that have\Nbeen there a thousand years. For a
Dialogue: 0,1:03:36.96,1:03:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,thousand years, mankind has been on\Ntheir knees thanking God,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:42.48,1:03:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,worshiping God.\NAnd
Dialogue: 0,1:03:49.35,1:03:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,if not sacred to begin with, they are\Ncertainly sacred by now.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:55.20,1:04:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Thousands and thousands of pilgrims over\Na thousand years have worshiped there
Dialogue: 0,1:04:02.24,1:04:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and they worship with incense\Nand the beauty of incredible music. The
Dialogue: 0,1:04:08.64,1:04:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,music that we play here\Nspeaks to me of the presence of God. It
Dialogue: 0,1:04:14.88,1:04:21.68,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates\N740 somewhere around in there. 700
Dialogue: 0,1:04:21.68,1:04:25.52,Default,,0,0,0,,to recognize.\NThe first way that most people can
Dialogue: 0,1:04:25.52,1:04:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,recognize God is through beauty. Through\Nbeauty and love. Maternal love is the
Dialogue: 0,1:04:32.72,1:04:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,first experience you have of God.\NYou think it's your mother, but it's God
Dialogue: 0,1:04:37.68,1:04:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,coming through your mother as in the\Nexpressionist maternal love, but it's
Dialogue: 0,1:04:41.52,1:04:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,your first experience of God.\NThe joy of life of adolescence is again
Dialogue: 0,1:04:49.11,1:04:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the joy of life\Nis another chance to experience the
Dialogue: 0,1:04:54.40,1:04:58.16,Default,,0,0,0,,presence of God.\NAnd then if one is fortunate, one is
Dialogue: 0,1:04:58.16,1:05:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,sensitive to beauty and you go into\Nexquisite states
Dialogue: 0,1:05:02.88,1:05:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,in nature or in music.\Nthe great moment in music that raises
Dialogue: 0,1:05:09.76,1:05:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,the hair on the back of your head and or\Nbreaks makes you break forth in tears.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:15.59,1:05:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not the music. It's the presence of\NGod as the beauty of music.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:22.24,1:05:27.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So beauty is one of the pathways to God.\NAnd all people spiritually evolved
Dialogue: 0,1:05:27.83,1:05:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,people appreciate beauty. On the other\Nhand, they're not attached to it.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:34.64,1:05:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You can be just as happy in a wood cabin\Nas you can in a cathedral.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:40.40,1:05:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,There's less housework.\NKeeping a cathedral neat and clean is a
Dialogue: 0,1:05:47.03,1:05:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,problem. Huh.\NSo
Dialogue: 0,1:05:51.20,1:05:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,um\Nthis is a question about the difference
Dialogue: 0,1:05:58.88,1:06:03.03,Default,,0,0,0,,between power and force which I think we\Ndid cover in the first lecture but we'll
Dialogue: 0,1:06:03.03,1:06:08.16,Default,,0,0,0,,recapitulate.\NPower
Dialogue: 0,1:06:08.16,1:06:13.11,Default,,0,0,0,,accomplishes what it does without\Nintending to by virtue of being what it
Dialogue: 0,1:06:13.11,1:06:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,is.\NGravity has no intention to lift a
Dialogue: 0,1:06:18.79,1:06:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,a nail from the floor. I mean magnetism\Nhas no intention of doing that. Gravity
Dialogue: 0,1:06:24.79,1:06:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,has no intention of pulling an apple out\Nof the tree.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:28.88,1:06:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Gravity, magnetism, the electrostatic\Nfield, the infinite universe
Dialogue: 0,1:06:35.76,1:06:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,are immensely powerful by virtue of that\Nwhich they are.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:41.28,1:06:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,All they have to do is be there.\NMahatma Gandhi stood there all 90 pounds
Dialogue: 0,1:06:48.07,1:06:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,of them and defeated the British Empire.\NHe calibrated 700 at the time and the
Dialogue: 0,1:06:56.40,1:07:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,British Empire calibrated 178 or 185 or\Nsomething.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:02.00,1:07:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,All Mahatma Gandhi had to do was just\Nsit there and not eat. And the British
Dialogue: 0,1:07:05.59,1:07:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Empire was defeated.\NHe didn't have to do anything. Gandhi
Dialogue: 0,1:07:11.11,1:07:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,did not fire a shot.\NSo power accomplishes effortlessly by
Dialogue: 0,1:07:20.96,1:07:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,virtue of that which it is. You don't\Nhave to feed it energy. It radiates
Dialogue: 0,1:07:26.40,1:07:30.79,Default,,0,0,0,,energy.\NIt accomplishes
Dialogue: 0,1:07:30.79,1:07:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,by virtue of the quality of that which\Nit is. It doesn't do anything. It
Dialogue: 0,1:07:37.11,1:07:43.03,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't have any intention.\NThose are all coming out of presumption
Dialogue: 0,1:07:43.03,1:07:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,of the human ego and projected which we\Nsee happening with God.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:49.20,1:07:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,We see that happening to the image of\NGod throughout time. All kinds of
Dialogue: 0,1:07:53.92,1:07:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,foibless and fallacies of the human ego\Nare projected onto God such as why
Dialogue: 0,1:07:58.79,1:08:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,questions.\NGravity is what it is and it's immensely
Dialogue: 0,1:08:05.20,1:08:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,powerful. It does it for millions and\Nbillions of eons without wearing itself
Dialogue: 0,1:08:11.44,1:08:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,out.\NEon after eon, the universe in its
Dialogue: 0,1:08:18.00,1:08:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,immense power determines.\NDoesn't determine by intention,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:24.79,1:08:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,but is that which\Nis the why of it all.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:32.40,1:08:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The why of it all is the is of it all.\NSo power then does what it does by
Dialogue: 0,1:08:39.67,1:08:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,virtue of its quality.\NI mean yes force is something else.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:47.67,1:08:55.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Force goes from here to there. Force\Nwears itself out. Force as we know from
Dialogue: 0,1:08:55.27,1:09:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,physics creates counterforce. This side\Narms and gets a militia. Automatically
Dialogue: 0,1:09:00.71,1:09:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,they get a militia. They get ballistic\Nmissiles. They get bombs. They get
Dialogue: 0,1:09:04.23,1:09:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,atomic bombs and so it escalates.\NThe Middle East is we shoot you, you
Dialogue: 0,1:09:10.64,1:09:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,shoot us, then we shoot you, you shoot\Nus, then you shoot us and we shoot you.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:18.15,1:09:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Sort of. So what?\NBut that's the nature of the game. So
Dialogue: 0,1:09:25.60,1:09:30.71,Default,,0,0,0,,force then exhausts itself. It's\Nlimited. The bullet eventually exhausts
Dialogue: 0,1:09:30.71,1:09:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,itself because as it goes through the\Nair, the air creates a counterforce. All
Dialogue: 0,1:09:36.64,1:09:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,force exhausts itself. The British I\Nmean the Holy Roman Empire was the
Dialogue: 0,1:09:42.00,1:09:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,greatest empire that ever existed\Nas far as length and success and
Dialogue: 0,1:09:47.83,1:09:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,eventually it just exhausted itself and\Nthe Roman Empire
Dialogue: 0,1:09:53.19,1:09:56.96,Default,,0,0,0,,uh collapsed.\NThe next great empire was the British
Dialogue: 0,1:09:56.96,1:10:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Empire. Ruled a quarter of the people of\Nthe earth.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:01.92,1:10:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And when I was young, the thought that\Nthe British Empire could ever come to an
Dialogue: 0,1:10:05.36,1:10:12.23,Default,,0,0,0,,end was not even thinkable.\NThe British Empire was infinitely
Dialogue: 0,1:10:12.23,1:10:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,powerful, the greatest navy on earth,\Netc. And the crown would consent
Dialogue: 0,1:10:17.12,1:10:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,continue forever, but it didn't.\NStill all that is based on force.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:25.84,1:10:31.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It expends itself, destroys itself. You\Nhave to constantly stoke it. You have to
Dialogue: 0,1:10:31.04,1:10:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,pour money, more bodies, more slaves,\Nmore energy, more taxes. It dissipates
Dialogue: 0,1:10:38.00,1:10:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,itself.\NThe value of spiritual work is that it
Dialogue: 0,1:10:44.64,1:10:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,takes you out of force into as you go\Nabove 200,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:50.64,1:10:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not what you do anymore that has\Nthe effect on your life and what
Dialogue: 0,1:10:55.44,1:11:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,happens. It's what you become.\NThe very fact that you are there already
Dialogue: 0,1:11:02.00,1:11:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,changes the nature of the event.\NYou don't even have to say anything. I
Dialogue: 0,1:11:10.64,1:11:13.60,Default,,0,0,0,,know meetings I've been to where there\Nwas one guy used to sit over in the
Dialogue: 0,1:11:13.60,1:11:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,corner. He never said anything for\Nyears.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:16.56,1:11:21.19,Default,,0,0,0,,One day he was missing.\NI miss this guy who' been sitting there
Dialogue: 0,1:11:21.19,1:11:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,for years saying nothing.\NSo obviously his presence was be
Dialogue: 0,1:11:27.44,1:11:34.23,Default,,0,0,0,,speaking something on some in some other\Ndimension of significance.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:34.23,1:11:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,People who are more spiritually evolved\Nthan have an effect that radiates out
Dialogue: 0,1:11:39.44,1:11:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,from them that is invisible, not\Ndiscernable, not logical, not traceable.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:45.12,1:11:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,But the very fact that you are there\Nalready changes the events. It the whole
Dialogue: 0,1:11:49.92,1:11:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,field changes due to your presence, due\Nto your prayers, due to your conscious
Dialogue: 0,1:11:55.04,1:12:00.08,Default,,0,0,0,,awareness, due to your inclusion of them\Ninto your thoughts. It already changes
Dialogue: 0,1:12:00.08,1:12:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,it.\NNow, a force cannot prevail against
Dialogue: 0,1:12:05.28,1:12:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,power.\NWhy? Because power is invincible.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:10.64,1:12:15.12,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing you can do to change the\Nfield of gravity.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:15.12,1:12:19.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You can throw billions of pounds of iron\Nand steel into the atmosphere and
Dialogue: 0,1:12:19.60,1:12:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,gravity doesn't change one iota.\NThe infinite power of God is totally
Dialogue: 0,1:12:24.88,1:12:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,unaffected by anything that occurs\Nwithin the universe.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:33.12,1:12:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Love is indestructible.\NTrue love is indestructible.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:44.80,1:12:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The lower levels then are ones of force,\Nviolence,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:51.12,1:12:56.08,Default,,0,0,0,,coercion,\Ntherefore of revolt.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:56.08,1:13:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,How one country can take over another\Ncountry with a different language and a
Dialogue: 0,1:13:00.32,1:13:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,different culture and a different\Nnationality and a different language and
Dialogue: 0,1:13:03.44,1:13:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,think they can succeed over long periods\Nof time is unbelievable.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:10.96,1:13:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,They aren't you and they're never going\Nto be you.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:15.52,1:13:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And they're never going to accept you're\Nruling them. They have a different
Dialogue: 0,1:13:19.52,1:13:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,color, a different language, different\Nmeaning, different terminology,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:22.48,1:13:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,different history. How can one country\Nthink it's going to succeed in capturing
Dialogue: 0,1:13:26.08,1:13:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,another country?\NObviously, it's it's time limited. It's
Dialogue: 0,1:13:32.23,1:13:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,not yours. Doesn't belong to you. So,\Nforce will not succeed over the long
Dialogue: 0,1:13:37.92,1:13:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,term.\NForce will not succeed over the long
Dialogue: 0,1:13:41.36,1:13:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,term. If force were more successful than\Npower, England never would have survived
Dialogue: 0,1:13:49.84,1:13:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,World War II.\NThe greatest war machine the world has
Dialogue: 0,1:13:55.28,1:13:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,ever seen\Narose out of an energy of 10 and
Dialogue: 0,1:13:59.28,1:14:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,whatever it was Hitler was at the time\Nand it was stood off by Winston
Dialogue: 0,1:14:05.19,1:14:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Churchill who calibrated at 510.\NIt was Britain didn't have a chance
Dialogue: 0,1:14:13.28,1:14:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,until 510 came up and began to speak for\NBritain.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:18.00,1:14:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,We will fight from the fields. We will\Nfight from the ditches. We will never
Dialogue: 0,1:14:22.08,1:14:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,surrender.\N510 then was
Dialogue: 0,1:14:27.60,1:14:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,with a very small air force was up\Nagainst the biggest military machine the
Dialogue: 0,1:14:32.64,1:14:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,world's ever seen\Nand survived. It did only because of 510
Dialogue: 0,1:14:38.64,1:14:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,leading the country.\N510 was leading the country.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:43.92,1:14:49.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Neville Chamberlain was like 170 or\Nsomething. with Neville Chamberlain
Dialogue: 0,1:14:49.12,1:14:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Britain would have lost.\NSo that which has power then energizes
Dialogue: 0,1:14:55.76,1:15:04.71,Default,,0,0,0,,all around it.\NThat's it energizes all around it.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:04.71,1:15:12.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It radiates forth without limitation.\NIt doesn't run out of energy. That which
Dialogue: 0,1:15:12.23,1:15:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,is power is inexhaustible\Nbecause it deres its power from
Dialogue: 0,1:15:19.44,1:15:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,the power of the truth God's truth. You\Nknow
Dialogue: 0,1:15:23.44,1:15:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,it the source of\Npower is the truth of the presence of
Dialogue: 0,1:15:29.44,1:15:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,God. So its source is continuous ongoing\Nand inexhaustible.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:39.52,1:15:46.32,Default,,0,0,0,,one can keep going forever.\NUh so that's sort of a summary of
Dialogue: 0,1:15:46.32,1:15:56.71,Default,,0,0,0,,difference between\Nwell I've been speaking about it says
Dialogue: 0,1:15:56.71,1:15:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,please speak about the nature of the\Nsoul. Well, that's what I'm talking
Dialogue: 0,1:15:59.28,1:16:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,about all day, right?\NBeneath thinking this, beneath
Dialogue: 0,1:16:10.48,1:16:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,feelingness, belief, all ideology,\Nbeneath all of form is that which is
Dialogue: 0,1:16:16.40,1:16:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,nonform. That which you call me, the\Nself.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:21.76,1:16:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,If I take off one leg, you're still me.\NIf I take off another leg, you're still
Dialogue: 0,1:16:24.96,1:16:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,me. If I take off an ear, you're still\Nme. The mirror is not the the me is not
Dialogue: 0,1:16:28.88,1:16:32.08,Default,,0,0,0,,the physical body because we can remove\Nit piece by piece and you'll still say
Dialogue: 0,1:16:32.08,1:16:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm me.\NDonovan's brain sitting there on things
Dialogue: 0,1:16:36.80,1:16:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,is I'm still me.\NThe sense of self then is independent of
Dialogue: 0,1:16:41.52,1:16:44.71,Default,,0,0,0,,physicality.\NTo know that you know you're not the
Dialogue: 0,1:16:44.71,1:16:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,physical body.\NThe sense of self does not change with
Dialogue: 0,1:16:49.76,1:16:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,thinkingness.\NCertainly with as as one gets older,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:55.28,1:16:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,one's thinking this can totally change\Nabout just about everything. And yet the
Dialogue: 0,1:16:59.76,1:17:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,sense of I the self is not changed. The\Notman, the self, the self with a capital
Dialogue: 0,1:17:07.12,1:17:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,S.\NIt seems strange to Christian tradition
Dialogue: 0,1:17:13.44,1:17:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,to call the presence of God within self\Nwith a capital S.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:19.92,1:17:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,sounds strange and somewhat foreign to\Nthose who are familiar with foreign
Dialogue: 0,1:17:24.80,1:17:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,spirit to literature. It is not strange\Nbut to people with a Christian
Dialogue: 0,1:17:29.19,1:17:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,background it seems strange to call\Nthe s the center of the core of one's
Dialogue: 0,1:17:34.96,1:17:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,existence\Nself with a capital S
Dialogue: 0,1:17:40.64,1:17:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,soul is more acceptable\Nto experience one's soul then one's
Dialogue: 0,1:17:48.32,1:17:55.19,Default,,0,0,0,,eternal soul as the one's reality would\Nbecome closer to common Christian
Dialogue: 0,1:17:55.19,1:18:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,thinking\NAs the as the awareness as the reality
Dialogue: 0,1:18:01.60,1:18:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,unfolds,\Nthere's no difference between that which
Dialogue: 0,1:18:05.12,1:18:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,you are. There is no difference between\NGod imminent and God transcendent. Those
Dialogue: 0,1:18:10.64,1:18:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,are just styles of languaging.\NThat which is the source of one's own
Dialogue: 0,1:18:16.64,1:18:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,existence is not different than that\Nwhich is the source and the essence of
Dialogue: 0,1:18:19.92,1:18:23.67,Default,,0,0,0,,all of\Nthe universe throughout all of time.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:23.67,1:18:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the first stunning awareness that\None ever even worried about this about
Dialogue: 0,1:18:28.56,1:18:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,life seems like the ultimate joke. How\None could have forgotten such an
Dialogue: 0,1:18:32.96,1:18:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,stunning and obvious reality is rather\Nstartling.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:38.64,1:18:52.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Um,\Na lot of funny questions.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:52.71,1:18:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,um that which shines forth that which\Nshines forth and gives one a sense of
Dialogue: 0,1:18:58.48,1:19:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,reality. You see you you accept a sense\Nof reality of your experience without
Dialogue: 0,1:19:04.08,1:19:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,question.\NWhy should you experience that which you
Dialogue: 0,1:19:10.23,1:19:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,experience as reality?\NIs there something out there that would
Dialogue: 0,1:19:14.64,1:19:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,give it a special sense of reality?\NYou see how you just assume that as a
Dialogue: 0,1:19:19.92,1:19:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,given?\NThat which you're looking for is that
Dialogue: 0,1:19:23.76,1:19:30.08,Default,,0,0,0,,which you overlook because you assume it\Nas a given. That which you assume as a
Dialogue: 0,1:19:30.08,1:19:35.67,Default,,0,0,0,,given is exactly that which you're\Ntrying to find.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:35.67,1:19:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like you're so used to living in\Nspace that you fail to recognize space
Dialogue: 0,1:19:39.44,1:19:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,anymore. You just take space for\Ngranted.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:45.67,1:19:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It's miraculous\Nthat one can experience
Dialogue: 0,1:19:50.80,1:19:56.96,Default,,0,0,0,,anything. It's miraculous to have the\Ncapacity to experience.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:56.96,1:20:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Does a rock experience?\NTo be conscious, to be aware, to
Dialogue: 0,1:20:02.56,1:20:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,experience one's own existence\Nis already a rather incredible event.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:10.32,1:20:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,But we take it for granted.\NBut once one grasps the significance of
Dialogue: 0,1:20:15.52,1:20:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,that, you realize\Nto exist and be aware that you exist is
Dialogue: 0,1:20:21.67,1:20:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,miraculous.\NThe miracle of one's own existence
Dialogue: 0,1:20:29.52,1:20:36.71,Default,,0,0,0,,of the Lord I am.\NWithout God, you would not exist in it.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:36.71,1:20:40.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And the source of one's existence is not\Ndifferent than the core of that which
Dialogue: 0,1:20:40.56,1:20:46.15,Default,,0,0,0,,you are.\NSo the soul cannot be not God. It can
Dialogue: 0,1:20:46.15,1:20:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,only be part and parcel of all that\Nexists
Dialogue: 0,1:20:50.88,1:21:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,in a particular\Nexpression.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:01.60,1:21:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody says, "How can you read without\Neyeglasses?" Oh, well that was a funny
Dialogue: 0,1:21:06.80,1:21:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,one, too.\NYeah, I think I told the story about the
Dialogue: 0,1:21:12.64,1:21:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,eyeglasses. You know, I had trifogals\Nand bifogals and I was the squinty kid.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:16.96,1:21:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't see the football coming till\Nit hit me in the nose. So, I was not a
Dialogue: 0,1:21:20.88,1:21:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,great football player.\NI didn't see it till it was there
Dialogue: 0,1:21:25.44,1:21:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,already. And uh\NI think it was a result of u a number of
Dialogue: 0,1:21:32.48,1:21:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,illnesses healed themselves\Nautomatically.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:35.44,1:21:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,But oh well that came about as a\Nconsequence of doing the course of
Dialogue: 0,1:21:38.64,1:21:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,miracles and in a class one time I was\Ndoing a class on the course of miracles
Dialogue: 0,1:21:42.96,1:21:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and I was talking about all the things\Nthat disappeared due to spiritual
Dialogue: 0,1:21:45.76,1:21:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,reality replacing illusion etc. One\Nillness after another cleared cleared
Dialogue: 0,1:21:51.76,1:21:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,cleared themsel due to spiritual work.\NSo somebody said well how come you still
Dialogue: 0,1:21:56.32,1:22:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,wear glasses? Well I always wore\Nglasses. In fact, by that time I had
Dialogue: 0,1:22:00.32,1:22:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,trifocals,\Nwhich are expensive, by the way, $450 or
Dialogue: 0,1:22:05.76,1:22:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,something. So they said, "Well, if\Nthat's so, then if everything is just a
Dialogue: 0,1:22:10.23,1:22:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,consequence of what you hold in mind,\Nhow come you still wear glasses and all
Dialogue: 0,1:22:14.00,1:22:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,these other things heal themselves?" And\NI said, "Well, I never thought of it as
Dialogue: 0,1:22:17.12,1:22:21.19,Default,,0,0,0,,an illness. I just thought of it as a\Nstructural defect, you know, like being
Dialogue: 0,1:22:21.19,1:22:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,short or tall or having a big nose or\Nsomething. I thought, well, there's a
Dialogue: 0,1:22:25.60,1:22:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,defect in the cornea and the retina or\Nsome weird thing in there
Dialogue: 0,1:22:30.96,1:22:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's mechanical. So, I said, "No, I\Nnever thought of that."
Dialogue: 0,1:22:35.36,1:22:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,But anyway, as she said that, I thought,\N"Well, yes, right." So, I took my
Dialogue: 0,1:22:39.28,1:22:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,glasses off and I put them in my pocket.\NAnd uh it was difficult driving without
Dialogue: 0,1:22:45.84,1:22:52.08,Default,,0,0,0,,being able to see where you were going.\NWhen I look back at myself now, I marvel
Dialogue: 0,1:22:52.08,1:22:56.71,Default,,0,0,0,,that I did such a thing. But my faith in\NGod, my faith in the course of miracles,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:56.71,1:23:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the faith in the miraculous was\Nabsolute.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:00.96,1:23:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, "By God, you're right." So I got\Nin the car. In fact, it was dark out and
Dialogue: 0,1:23:06.00,1:23:11.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I could only see where I needed to see.\NIt was really bizarre. The whole road
Dialogue: 0,1:23:11.60,1:23:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,was fog except for like if the edge of\Nthe road was there driving around, you
Dialogue: 0,1:23:17.44,1:23:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,know, up to up around Jerome and crap\Nlike that. So there's the edge of the
Dialogue: 0,1:23:21.12,1:23:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,cliff right there.\NI would only see what I needed to see
Dialogue: 0,1:23:24.88,1:23:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,when I needed to see it. So, uh, if I\Nlooked around this room, I wouldn't be
Dialogue: 0,1:23:29.60,1:23:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,able to see anything. It was all It's\Nall just gray fuzz. And so, uh, I
Dialogue: 0,1:23:35.36,1:23:40.23,Default,,0,0,0,,somehow went from one place to another\Nand I would just see what I needed to
Dialogue: 0,1:23:40.23,1:23:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,see. When I had one time, I had to turn\Ninto Unity Church, make a left turn off
Dialogue: 0,1:23:43.92,1:23:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,89A,\Nand just as I needed to make the left
Dialogue: 0,1:23:48.40,1:23:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,turn, I had no idea where the road was.\NI couldn't see it. some cars spotlight
Dialogue: 0,1:23:53.60,1:23:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,headlights shown right on the turn in\Nand I just turned over there and went in
Dialogue: 0,1:23:57.04,1:24:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,there. It was\Nwent to Unity Church for the glass. So
Dialogue: 0,1:24:01.76,1:24:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,anyway, this I lived that way\Nand I surrendered to it. I said, "Well,"
Dialogue: 0,1:24:07.44,1:24:10.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and it didn't get any better, by the\Nway.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:10.80,1:24:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The weeks the weeks went by and uh it\Njust stayed that way. And but
Dialogue: 0,1:24:16.56,1:24:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,peculiarly, I could see what I needed to\Nsee when I needed to see it.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:21.84,1:24:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like you could you couldn't see\Nwhat you needed to save your life until
Dialogue: 0,1:24:26.63,1:24:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,you actually had to see it. You know,\Nyou could see the fire extinguisher just
Dialogue: 0,1:24:30.32,1:24:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,as the fire started, but not before\Nthe timing was exact.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:37.04,1:24:41.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You couldn't anticipate God. You\Ncouldn't. And I learned how to live in
Dialogue: 0,1:24:41.19,1:24:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the exact instant of the moment\Ninstead of trying to gain control over
Dialogue: 0,1:24:47.04,1:24:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,the next instant to ensure your own\Nsurvival. his you surrendered your
Dialogue: 0,1:24:52.63,1:24:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,survival to God.\NIf the will of God was that you
Dialogue: 0,1:24:56.32,1:25:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,survived, then you survived. And if it\Nwas otherwise, then you wouldn't. If you
Dialogue: 0,1:25:02.32,1:25:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,went off the cliff, you went off the\Ncliff. So if you go off the cliff, you
Dialogue: 0,1:25:05.52,1:25:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,go off the cliff.\NThe surrender was absolute.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:10.48,1:25:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,One day I was standing in the kitchen of\Na friend
Dialogue: 0,1:25:14.40,1:25:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and standing in the kitchen chattering\Naway. All of a sudden, I could see
Dialogue: 0,1:25:19.04,1:25:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,everything. All of a sudden, I could see\Nthe calendar all the way across the room
Dialogue: 0,1:25:22.80,1:25:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and read the read the calendar across\Nthe room. It was incredible. And
Dialogue: 0,1:25:29.44,1:25:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,so I've got boxes full of glasses.\NAnyway,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:34.32,1:25:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I now use them for reading at times\Nbecause it saves energy. I can read
Dialogue: 0,1:25:38.00,1:25:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,without them, but it's it saves energy\Nif I've got to read a lot of stuff with
Dialogue: 0,1:25:41.92,1:25:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,it. So, that was just one experience of\Nthe course of miracles.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:47.76,1:25:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there any benefit in knowing about\Nyour past lives? Uh, you must have
Dialogue: 0,1:25:52.80,1:26:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,missed the lecture on karma.\NA karmic event in itself. By the way,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:08.15,1:26:12.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I said people who are seriously\Nspiritually committed, you've only got
Dialogue: 0,1:26:12.63,1:26:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,so much time and so much energy. So you\Nreally want to use it to the best
Dialogue: 0,1:26:17.44,1:26:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,purpose available. You don't have all\Nday every day around the clock to focus
Dialogue: 0,1:26:21.44,1:26:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,on spiritual work. Most people have a\Ncertain limited amount of time and
Dialogue: 0,1:26:24.80,1:26:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,energy. You don't want to waste it.\NSome degree of karmic research can save
Dialogue: 0,1:26:30.32,1:26:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,a lot of time, can save a lot of guilt,\Nsave a lot of self-rermination.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:35.19,1:26:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh once you see how a certain pattern\Nevolved throughout a series of
Dialogue: 0,1:26:39.44,1:26:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,lifetimes, you get a certain aha\Nfeeling.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:43.92,1:26:48.71,Default,,0,0,0,,you're okay with it. There's an\Nacceptance. There's a logical
Dialogue: 0,1:26:48.71,1:26:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,obviousness about it.\NUm when at a certain level of
Dialogue: 0,1:26:53.19,1:26:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness, which I think we\Ncalibrate around 600, uh there's a
Dialogue: 0,1:26:57.60,1:27:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,recall of those lives and the\Nsignificance and what they were about
Dialogue: 0,1:27:02.23,1:27:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and you see the pattern in this life.\NI think everybody is aware of certain
Dialogue: 0,1:27:07.28,1:27:12.08,Default,,0,0,0,,patterns in your life, right? there\Ncertain recurrent patterns and you say,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:12.08,1:27:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, this can't be just due to\Nchance.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:16.56,1:27:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,14 car accidents in a row. There's got\Nto be something.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:22.32,1:27:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You notice a repetitious pattern. You\Nnotice that it follows sort of a
Dialogue: 0,1:27:25.76,1:27:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,non-logic. Sort of a non-logic. People\Nsay, I keep mirroring the same kind of
Dialogue: 0,1:27:30.40,1:27:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,person. You know, why is that? People\Nlook for psychological reasons. Well,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:35.52,1:27:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,the psychological reason is karmic.\NSo past life regression I think has a
Dialogue: 0,1:27:42.48,1:27:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,practical use at times inologic research\Nuh can define a certain lifetime. Very
Dialogue: 0,1:27:49.76,1:27:53.84,Default,,0,0,0,,often you intuit it that that's what\Nit's about and then you check it out
Dialogue: 0,1:27:53.84,1:28:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,kinesiology and it says yes it's about\Nthat. So now you feel more okay with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:00.40,1:28:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I mean?\NI think it's uh a matter of efficiency.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:12.48,1:28:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll probably arrive at the same\Nunderstanding sooner or later, but it
Dialogue: 0,1:28:18.56,1:28:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,can save you many years of suffering\Nunnecessarily.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:23.60,1:28:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Suffering unnecessarily.\NYou can say, "Why was I addicted in this
Dialogue: 0,1:28:28.32,1:28:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,lifetime? Why? Why me? Why me? Why me?"\NAnd then you find from karmic research
Dialogue: 0,1:28:33.44,1:28:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,that you died five or six times out of\Naddiction. This is your sixth and
Dialogue: 0,1:28:37.36,1:28:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,seventh. This is your last shot at\Nsobriety. This time you either surrender
Dialogue: 0,1:28:41.44,1:28:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,to God or you're going to go down again.\NUh death by addiction. So you see it
Dialogue: 0,1:28:47.28,1:28:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,makes begins to make sense. So you stop\Nfeeling sorry for yourself. A lot of
Dialogue: 0,1:28:51.52,1:28:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,resentments are uh disappear.\NA lot of explanation feeling sorry for
Dialogue: 0,1:28:56.40,1:28:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,yourself for certain physical ailments\Ndisappear.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:59.84,1:29:04.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And I've explained some of those in my\Nown personal past lifetime experiences
Dialogue: 0,1:29:04.56,1:29:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,uh as they recurred in this lifetime.\NYou know, you even see it at the time
Dialogue: 0,1:29:09.28,1:29:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,it's happening. You even see it at the\Ntime of the surgery without anesthesia.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:13.52,1:29:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw exactly what had happened and how\Nit had happened in great detail.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:19.04,1:29:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,There was that took away any feeling of\Ninjustice that people that don't
Dialogue: 0,1:29:24.63,1:29:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,understand karmic\Nyou might say karmic laws uh are
Dialogue: 0,1:29:30.00,1:29:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,suffering from a sense of injustice all\Nthe time. They're always entitled and
Dialogue: 0,1:29:33.67,1:29:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,they're always getting their feelings\Nhurt and they really have a miserable
Dialogue: 0,1:29:37.60,1:29:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,life of it all.\NAnd with a little karmic research, you
Dialogue: 0,1:29:43.76,1:29:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,stop feeling sorry for yourself. Yes,\Nyou were an SOB in a lot of lifetimes
Dialogue: 0,1:29:48.23,1:29:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and yes, that is what you did to others.\NOh, okay. That makes it a little easier
Dialogue: 0,1:29:53.28,1:30:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,to accept, right? All right.\Num
Dialogue: 0,1:30:02.40,1:30:07.67,Default,,0,0,0,,the asking for grace. We said that\Nprayer sec uh
Dialogue: 0,1:30:07.67,1:30:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,sanctifying one's life by committing it\Nto God out of reverence for and
Dialogue: 0,1:30:14.00,1:30:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,thankfulness for one's own existence\Nuh automatically has a consequence in
Dialogue: 0,1:30:20.32,1:30:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the field of consciousness.\NIn talking about karma, we say spiritual
Dialogue: 0,1:30:27.52,1:30:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the spiritual will is what really sets\Nkarmic
Dialogue: 0,1:30:31.36,1:30:35.28,Default,,0,0,0,,balance.\NWould a person who calibrates a 700
Dialogue: 0,1:30:35.28,1:30:50.08,Default,,0,0,0,,dream differently? I don't know.\NAnything spiritually dedicated
Dialogue: 0,1:30:50.08,1:30:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,is probably equal to anything else you\Ndo that's spiritually dedicated.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:56.40,1:31:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether it's rotating a prayer wheel,\Nwhether it's sewing for the poor,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:05.19,1:31:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,whether it's just doing the most honest\Nday's work you can do,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:10.00,1:31:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,whether it's trying to respect mankind\Neven though at times mankind seems so.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:15.92,1:31:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise\Nto try to comprehend how can I love Mid
Dialogue: 0,1:31:19.92,1:31:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Len, you know what I mean? How can I\Nforgive this guy? Especially if you a
Dialogue: 0,1:31:23.76,1:31:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,relative of yours went down in the whole\Nthing.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:26.96,1:31:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,How can I overcome this hatred, this\Nanger, this resentment?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:32.23,1:31:36.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So s even if it isn't our own ego, it's\Nthe collective ego of society that
Dialogue: 0,1:31:36.71,1:31:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,reflects back to us the necessity for\Nconstant spiritual growth. Huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:44.56,1:31:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,We even if it isn't in our lifetime, we\Nwitness it out there. And certainly TV,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:50.32,1:31:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I think, is exhilarated spiritual growth\Nbecause you're constantly confronted
Dialogue: 0,1:31:54.96,1:32:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,with the the projection of the ego out\Ninto the world, expressing itself
Dialogue: 0,1:32:01.12,1:32:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,uh in the history, the current history\Nof mankind. It's always projecting
Dialogue: 0,1:32:05.04,1:32:12.23,Default,,0,0,0,,itself out there. And so you have a the\Ncapacity to benefit by by it, but
Dialogue: 0,1:32:12.23,1:32:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,without actually experiencing it. You\Ndon't have to be there in the Middle
Dialogue: 0,1:32:16.88,1:32:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,East war and get shot and shoot back and\Nforth. You can witness it and come to a
Dialogue: 0,1:32:22.88,1:32:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,way of transcending the whole thing\Nwithout actually having to be on the
Dialogue: 0,1:32:28.88,1:32:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,battlefield. So in a certain way, our\Nmodern lecture uh
Dialogue: 0,1:32:34.80,1:32:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,our modern media I think speeds up\Nspiritual work because you're bombarded
Dialogue: 0,1:32:40.00,1:32:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,with uh spiritual dilemmas and\Nprovocations and
Dialogue: 0,1:32:45.67,1:32:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,all right\Nwe can't do much more than that with
Dialogue: 0,1:32:49.60,1:32:55.67,Default,,0,0,0,,that today because\Nthere questions we didn't resolve
Dialogue: 0,1:32:55.67,1:33:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,no why questions. Oh, God bless you.\NIs there any questions we did not
Dialogue: 0,1:33:02.56,1:33:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,resolve because we want to bring it to a\Nclosure and then we'll have people come
Dialogue: 0,1:33:08.80,1:33:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,up and I'll greet you all and hug you\Nall and sign any books or anything. Have
Dialogue: 0,1:33:14.00,1:33:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,someone speak for you. Please.\N>> Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:25.04,1:33:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,>> What does he say?\NUh,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:35.19,1:33:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,by virtue of what? I don't know.\NBy virtue of
Dialogue: 0,1:33:41.92,1:33:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,hitting the absolute bottom, beyond all\Nbottoms,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:46.48,1:33:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,beyond all hope.\NOnce
Dialogue: 0,1:33:51.12,1:33:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,you get out of the hell of time and\Ntorture and
Dialogue: 0,1:33:55.12,1:34:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,pain and suffering and all that,\Nyou get to the serious levels of hell
Dialogue: 0,1:34:00.15,1:34:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,which are beyond time.\NThe dreadfulness of absolute
Dialogue: 0,1:34:09.04,1:34:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,hopelessness and aloneeness\Ncompletely deserted by God forever
Dialogue: 0,1:34:17.52,1:34:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,is a horror that cannot be described.\NAnd out of the the abysmal agony which
Dialogue: 0,1:34:23.60,1:34:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,went on for eons,\Nthe lower levels of hell have nothing to
Dialogue: 0,1:34:27.84,1:34:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,do with time. You're not there for 5\Nyears or 20 years.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:31.60,1:34:38.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It goes on just like the upper space is\Nforeverness.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:38.15,1:34:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The condemnation is forever.\NOut of that came the voice from within.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:48.23,1:34:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,If there is a God, I ask him to help me.\NIt came out. The voice came of its own
Dialogue: 0,1:34:56.00,1:35:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,from within the spirit.\NI guess the sincerity of it
Dialogue: 0,1:35:04.23,1:35:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,uh caught the attention of a passing\Narchangel
Dialogue: 0,1:35:09.36,1:35:14.63,Default,,0,0,0,,who glanced that away and\Nan archangel at 50 thou calibrates
Dialogue: 0,1:35:14.63,1:35:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,50,000 over\Njust to be noticed in passing probably
Dialogue: 0,1:35:18.96,1:35:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,totally transforms everything because\Nthat much power is like
Dialogue: 0,1:35:23.28,1:35:30.63,Default,,0,0,0,,100,000 volts and it just in one spark\Nis totally transformative
Dialogue: 0,1:35:30.63,1:35:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,but I can't um\NI can't tell you any more than the
Dialogue: 0,1:35:35.12,1:35:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,experience of it the experiential\Nsequence there was one more and then
Dialogue: 0,1:35:38.48,1:35:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll go yes\N>> spiritual will is what sets calibrated
Dialogue: 0,1:35:51.76,1:35:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,level of consciousness\Nwhat sets your calibrated level of
Dialogue: 0,1:35:55.36,1:36:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness is not the act but the\Nintention behind the act.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:04.88,1:36:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The freedom of choice is the one last\Nfreedom one has.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:09.92,1:36:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Even in the very depths of hell, there\Nwas still the freedom of choice.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:15.36,1:36:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,At that point, God could have been\Nrefused forever out of bitterness and
Dialogue: 0,1:36:19.04,1:36:22.23,Default,,0,0,0,,hatred,\Nand I would have then become a member of
Dialogue: 0,1:36:22.23,1:36:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the lower astral.\Nthose who have refused God
Dialogue: 0,1:36:29.28,1:36:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,live there.\NSo the freedom of choice was is is
Dialogue: 0,1:36:35.12,1:36:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,always present. Even as somebody is\Nchopping you up,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:40.63,1:36:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,you can transcend the instant.\NI respected the valor of the guy as he
Dialogue: 0,1:36:47.04,1:36:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,killed me.\NI really loved him in a way.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:51.92,1:36:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I could see\Nthe sincerity and power and total
Dialogue: 0,1:36:57.60,1:37:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,commitment of the spiritual warrior in\Nthis guy.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:01.52,1:37:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, he was for God if it cost him my\Nlife and he knew it was costing his
Dialogue: 0,1:37:06.88,1:37:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,life. I guaranteed that\Nand he guaranteed the end of my life.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:13.04,1:37:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So, but in the moment of killing each\Nother,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:17.60,1:37:22.71,Default,,0,0,0,,we like um\Nrespected each other at a very high
Dialogue: 0,1:37:22.71,1:37:28.23,Default,,0,0,0,,level.\NI recognized his devotion to God and I
Dialogue: 0,1:37:28.23,1:37:32.08,Default,,0,0,0,,died\Ncomplimented that I was killed by
Dialogue: 0,1:37:32.08,1:37:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,somebody who killed me out of their\Ndevotion to God and he was equally
Dialogue: 0,1:37:35.52,1:37:40.56,Default,,0,0,0,,honored by my killing him. So, we were\Nof service to each other. You might say
Dialogue: 0,1:37:40.56,1:37:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the choices that are available to you to\Neveryone depends on your level of
Dialogue: 0,1:37:45.52,1:37:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,evolution of consciousness.\NIf you trans if you have reached the
Dialogue: 0,1:37:51.52,1:37:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,point of spiritual nobility,\Nthen that choice to honor the spiritual
Dialogue: 0,1:37:57.44,1:38:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,commitment of what the world would call\Nyour opponent is open to you. From this
Dialogue: 0,1:38:02.32,1:38:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,level, you would only hate him. You\Nunderstand? So the options that are open
Dialogue: 0,1:38:07.52,1:38:12.71,Default,,0,0,0,,to you reflect the level of your own\Ndevelopment of your own consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:12.71,1:38:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So one reason to evolve in consciousness\Nis because the choices that are open to
Dialogue: 0,1:38:17.28,1:38:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,you are not open to people who haven't\Nreached that point. The choice of
Dialogue: 0,1:38:21.44,1:38:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,forgiving people is not open.\NMajority of mankind doesn't think of
Dialogue: 0,1:38:26.40,1:38:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,forgiving your enemy. Right?\NThat's not a prevailing attitude.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:33.67,1:38:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you hate it for for many\Ngenerations, right? Middle East, they
Dialogue: 0,1:38:37.84,1:38:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,just go on hating each other generation\Nafter generation, century after century
Dialogue: 0,1:38:42.00,1:38:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,for a thousand years. They don't stop.\NSo the option to not hate doesn't
Dialogue: 0,1:38:48.08,1:38:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,apparently is not there with the\Nexception of individuals within within
Dialogue: 0,1:38:52.56,1:38:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,there who probably evolve as a result of\Nall this and say, you know, this is
Dialogue: 0,1:38:56.80,1:39:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,stupid and now they've got an option to\Ncop out. But until you get unhooked from
Dialogue: 0,1:39:03.36,1:39:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,that lower energy field of hatred, if\Nyou're caught in the spleen, you're
Dialogue: 0,1:39:06.71,1:39:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,caught on the spleen. So to one who is\Ncaught in the spleen, you don't have the
Dialogue: 0,1:39:12.00,1:39:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,option of loving. It's not within your\Ncapacity.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:17.36,1:39:21.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So the value of spiritually evolved\Npeople to each other is they radiate
Dialogue: 0,1:39:21.19,1:39:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,that capacity in into your aura. So the\Nshared aura of spiritually evolved
Dialogue: 0,1:39:26.48,1:39:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,people brings to you you know you've got\Nthe option of forgiveness no matter how
Dialogue: 0,1:39:31.92,1:39:36.63,Default,,0,0,0,,bad it is you know uh there is no\Njustified resentment the option to
Dialogue: 0,1:39:36.63,1:39:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,forgive is cap is capable.\NSo we'll just say one last thing and
Dialogue: 0,1:39:41.84,1:39:48.63,Default,,0,0,0,,then we'll conclude. All that is\Nrequired is already present within you.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:48.63,1:39:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The love of God is so powerful, so deep,\Nso innate
Dialogue: 0,1:39:55.04,1:40:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,to the very essence of your beingness\Nthat if you find it, you will find that
Dialogue: 0,1:40:00.96,1:40:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,within yourself there is the power and\Nthe willingness to surrender
Dialogue: 0,1:40:06.48,1:40:13.11,Default,,0,0,0,,all including life itself to God. There\Nis within yourself already a powerful
Dialogue: 0,1:40:13.11,1:40:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,devotion.\NYou say, "I don't have the power to do
Dialogue: 0,1:40:17.11,1:40:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,that." If you summon it forth within\Nyourself is already existent.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:24.96,1:40:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,For thee, oh Lord God, do I lay down my\Nlife in all of its details.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:35.60,1:40:41.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The power of that devotion lies within\Nall of you and it's the guarantee of
Dialogue: 0,1:40:41.19,1:40:44.52,Default,,0,0,0,,your salvation.
